According to the [[2000 United States census|2000 U.S. census]], there were 2,286 people, 903 households, and 582 families residing in the town.<ref name="GR2" /> The population density was {{convert|618.7|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. There were 1,045 housing units at an average density of {{convert|282.8|/sqmi|/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of the town was 77.21% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 13.52% [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]], 0.61% [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]], 0.31% [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], 7.17% from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 1.18% from two or more races. [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]] of any race were 10.80% of the population. In 2020, its population was 2,491;<ref name=":0" /> at the [[2020 United States census|2020 U.S. census]], its racial and ethnic makeup was predominantly [[Non-Hispanic whites|non-Hispanic white]].

In 2000, the median income for a household in the town was $28,824, and the median income for a family was $36,150. Males had a median income of $30,132 versus $18,707 for females. The [[per capita income]] for the town was $16,186. About 14.9% of families and 17.8% of the population were below the [[poverty line]], including 22.6% of those under age 18 and 16.3% of those age 65 or over. The 2020 [[American Community Survey]] determined the median household income was $56,016.<ref>{{Cite web |title=2020 ACS Financial Characteristics |url=https://data.census.gov/cedsci/table?q=Mount%20Vernon%20town,%20Texas%20income&tid=ACSST5Y2020.S2503 |access-date=May 13, 2022 |website=data.census.gov}}</ref>

